# Password Strength Tester

This project is a web application that allows users to test the strength of their passwords. It evaluates passwords based on criteria such as length, complexity, use of special characters, and common patterns.

## Features
- Checks password length
- Checks for uppercase letters, numbers, and special characters
- Provides feedback on password strength

## Technologies Used
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Backend: Node.js (Express)


## Setup Instructions

### Node.js
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/password-strength-tester.git
``` 
   cd password-strength-tester

npm install
npm start

Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000.



If this won't work then: node app.js
